tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, low total CO₂, and low urine specific gravity, suggesting impaired renal function and possible metabolic acidosis. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, ketonuria, glucosuria, and abnormal urine appearance, raising concern for nephropathy and possible dehydration or catabolic state. HbA1c is low, indicating no chronic hyperglycemia. Recommend further evaluation of renal function, hydration status, and possible underlying causes (e.g., diabetes, infection, or other renal pathology).
